  "note": "FY2018 NEP was never published as Excel \u2014 only as scanned PDFs. NEP totals were OCR-extracted from NEP-2018 Volume I pp.21-22 (dept-level summary) and from per-dept PDFs at /NEP2018/{DEPT}/{DEPT}.pdf GENERAL SUMMARY pages (last page of each) for the top-5 depts: DEPED, DPWH, DILG, DND, DSWD. NEP-side parquet emits program-level rows: where direct OCR of NEP body pages yielded valid program-table rows (DEPED OSEC p6; DILG OSEC p4-7) and the parsed UACS code matched a GAA-2018 program_id, those amounts are taken as-is; the remaining agency/dept budget is then apportioned across GAA-2018 program structure (proportional to GAA shares). DPWH OSEC apportioning falls back fully to GAA structure because DPWH GAA-2018 has 20,597 project-level UACS ids while NEP summarises at PREXC program-group level only \u2014 direct UACS matching produced spurious reshuffle. Result: program_pct reflects inter-program reshuffle visible at this granularity (dominated by Automatic Appropriations / ALGU / IRA umbrella vs distributed GAA categories). leaf_pct is 100% because NEP-2018 rows have null operunit/region/fund/object \u2014 those line-item dimensions are not available in the source scans. Parser changes: pdf_to_rows.merge_uacs_wrap_rows() handles forward-wrap row association on NEP-2018 body pages (UACS code on visual line 1 + amounts on visual line 2). Backup of prior v2 parquet: etl/nep_2018.parquet.bak-prexc-attempt."
